HR NO. 72 ENROLLED
WHEREAS, the Future Farmers of America national chapter awards program
recognizes outstanding chapters that show innovation in growing leaders, strengthening
agriculture, and building communities; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of their exceptional hard work and initiative, Sophia and
Layla won the building communities division national championship award from the Future
Farmers of America for the Coastal Restoration Heroes program they created.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Sophia Patout and Layla Porter on their
exceptional leadership, environmental stewardship, and civic responsibility and for winning
the Future Farmers of America building communities national championship for their
Coastal Restoration Heroes program.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
Sophia Patout and Layla Porter.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
